
[1]desk

   DESK, n.

   1. An inclining table for the use of writers and readers; usually made
   with a box or drawer underneath, and sometimes with a book-case above.

   2. The pulpit in a church, and figuratively the clerical profession.
   The man appears well in the desk. He intends one son for the bar, and
   another for the desk.

                DESK, v.t. To shut up in a desk; to treasure.
